While we&#x27;re on the subject, here&#x27;s my super nitpicky complaint abour mori: the use of snake_case when almost all JS is camelCase.<p>In the simple little project where I used mori, I did this:<p><pre><code>    const {
      get,
      conj,
      js_to_clj: map,
      clj_to_js: pretty
    } = mori;
</code></pre>
But I bet you lose a surprisingly large number of JS devs due to just having the &quot;wrong&quot; names. Maybe I should publish a camel-case-mori module on npm...
